<subSubSection id="D169C321970ADC1082DE291284030008" pageId="4" pageNumber="41" type="description">
<paragraph id="3A568700701B81117866A7EBBF51FB2A" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="18FBEB55A5BC78F6FA606FB23BA42CD9" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">-The generic description applies. Bases of hind wings in mature adult dark red, yellow, or orange. Abdominal tergites banded in dark blue.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F1D5B03A05E78FA0F16B414A17F2BAA4" pageId="4" pageNumber="41" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="402DB5EB85FBE6900AC2C04F5751332B" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="60074E3F89CF3FE0E25EB9CD00E3A7E5" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">-Found principally in the African Sahel region, from SENEGAL to CHAD, but also occurs in D.R. CONGO, MALAWI, and UGANDA: Adjumani and W. Busoga.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="13A625DA6BA92825271EC527470E1065" pageId="4" pageNumber="41" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="B1A31A1221FFA446660C3436330C3C09" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="489990862013484D69B1879E91CDD723" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">
- 
<bibRefCitation id="45672569CE5CDC295A81DC501F2D4895" author="Fishpool, LDC" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de l'Institut Fondamental d'Afrique Noire" pageId="49" pageNumber="86" pagination="275 - 410" title="The grasshopper faunas of the savannas of Mali, Niger, Benin and Togo." volume="43" year="1984">Fishpool and Popov (1984)</bibRefCitation>
record the species in MALI as being gramnivorous and mesophilous. In 
<taxonomicName id="68FFC58837CBF35D0D55074A2C816CDD" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Uganda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Uganda" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Uganda</taxonomicName>
it occurs in dry grass savanna.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
